 set the guild policies and make changes as they see needed. Changes to guild policy requires unanymous agreement among the council members. The council also handles guild disciplinary issues and must act unanymously.<br><br>Individual Council Member Responsibilities:<br><br>Guild Banker - Kazan:<br>- Store guild items<br>- Track the guild items and maintain a list of what items we have and which loot pool they belong (guild only - main character, guild only - twink, for public sale)<br>- Track platinum reserves<br>- Manage sale of unneeded items<br>- Manage process for receiving and delivering items and cash to and from guild bank (reimbursements etc.)<br><br>Guild Raid Planner - Swiller:<br>- Manage raiding calendar<br>- Publicize raid events<br>- Research new areas and stratagies<br>- Choose raid leaders and ensure raid leaders are properly trained and instructed<br>- Train guild members who wish to learn how to lead raids<br>- Announce who is rolling for a drop and announce winner in DKP Manager's absence.<br><br>DKP Manager - Gminsh:<br>- Track individual guild member DKP bank balances and purchases<br>- Maintain DKP data<br>- Report DKP data to guild<br>- Maintain DKP item price list<br>- Maintain DKP raid value list<br>- Announce who is rolling for a specific drop and call the winner of the random<br><br>Epic Coordinator - Sirakova:<br>- Manage tracking of individual guild member epic progress<br>- Understand each epic quest and involvement of the raids<br>- Work with raid planner to get epic raids scheduled<br>- Motivate individual members to complete non-raid portions of epic quest.<br>- When SoL released, research epic armor quests<br><br>Public Relations Specialist - Slaas:<br>- Manage guild public relations<br>- Develop and maintain positive relations with other guilds and groups<br>- Resolve issues and complaints<br>- Manage inter-guild negotiation<br><br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Class Leaders</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Class leaders are responsible for the guild members of their particular class. They work with these players individually to train, motivate and ensure that they are adding value to the guild. They also are responsible for recruiting new members of their class.<br><br>Class Leader Responsibilities:<br><br>- Track talent level of players of their class<br>- Initiate recruitment process for players of their class<br>- Research and train guild members of their class<br>- Ensure players of their class understand their role and responsibilities on raids -- especially guests<br><br>(A list of class leaders is being developed.)<br><br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Raid Leaders</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Raid leaders are the players who actually run our raids.  We have 2-3 raid leaders who run the majority of our raids, but we encourage all our members to develop raid leading abilities as this is good experience.<br><br>Raid Leader Responsibilities:<br><br>- Work with the Raid Planner to fully understand the raid strategies<br>- Manage assigning of groups (do or delegate)<br>- Lead the raid<br>- Ensure all loot is delivered to guild banker <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub46.ezboard.com/uslaas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Slaas</A> at: 8/24/01 12:37:10 am<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=5.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.showNextMessage?topicID=5.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic><img src=http://www.sacrosanctguild.com/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.threadContr